    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="840"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d840">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 862.85/412</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Commercial Adviser of the British Embassy</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_CSR1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crawford</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Assistant to the Counselor for the
                        Department of State</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_AG1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Auchincloss</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 22, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_AG1"
                            >Auchincloss</persName>
                    </hi>: We have received a telegram from the Foreign Office to the effect that
                    the British authorities concur in the recognition of the transfer of flag in the
                    case of the three Chilean ships, <hi rend="italic">Karnak, Alda</hi> and <hi
                        rend="italic">Göttingen</hi> on the understanding that the vessels will
                    carry no crew, officers or passengers of enemy nationality and that they will
                    transport nitrates to the United States.</p>
                <p>The Foreign Office also add that they thoroughly agree with your proposal for
                    mutual consultation between our two Governments before giving any definite reply
                    in the event of applications being <pb facs="0917" n="1751" xml:id="pg_1751"/>
                    made by South American Governments in the future for transfer of flag.</p>
                <p>Yours very truly,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">R. S. Hudson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/> (In the absence of <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_CSR1">Sir R.
                        Crawford</persName>)</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
